I designed a slot-aware summarization pipeline that integrates SBERT-based slot extraction and a weighted beam search algorithm to preserve domain-critical information in KoBART-generated summaries of social welfare policy documents.
Through an 8-condition comparative experiment, slot-constraint application yielded statistically significant gains (p < 0.05) on BERTScore and RDASS in 6 of 8 cases, showing that defining domain-essential information units outweighs model architecture and decoding strategy. I led the full pipeline design, experiments, and cross-validation, and verified statistical significance with paired-sample t-tests and bootstrap resampling.
